Traveling in and out of Gauteng is permitted for hunting, but only for the purpose of obtaining meat for consumption and culling. eNCA's Dan speaks to Acting Deputy Director General for Regulatory Compliance and Sector Monitoring at the Department of Forestry, Fisheries, Vanessa Bendeman. for more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Traveling in and out of Gauteng is permitted for hunting, but only for the purpose of obtaining meat for consumption and culling. READ: COVID-19 | WATCH | Gauteng ramps up vaccine drive This was clarified by Environmental Affairs Minister Barbara Creecy on Monday. Travel for leisure in and out of the province is still not allowed. Watch the video above for more details.